text: Arizona's 30th Legislative District is one of 30 in the state, situated in central Maricopa County. As of 2018 there are 29 precincts in the district, with a total registered voter population of 80,872. ==Political representation== The district is represented for the 2019-2021 Legislative Session in the State Senate by Tony Navarrete (D) and in the House of Representatives by Robert Meza (D) and Raquel Teran (D). ==References== Category:Maricopa County, Arizona Category:Arizona legislative districts
title: Arizona's 30th legislative district
